        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 10:50AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1050 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
northwest of Kiowa, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Arpelar...                        Mcalester...
Pittsburg...                      Crowder...
Kiowa...                          Haywood...
Blocker...                        Dow...
Bache...                          Arrowhead State Park...
Hartshorne...                     Haileyville...
Mcalester Regional Airport...     Krebs...
Alderson...                       Blanco...
Ashland...                        Savanna...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
